1 insurer shall immediately cancel the bail bond producer's appointment. The
2 bail bond producer may be reappointed only upon certification by the former
3 insurer that all forfeitures and judgments on bonds written by the bail bond
4 producer have been discharged.
5 (3) The appointing insurer or bail bond producer may appeal to the
6 commissioner no later than ten days after receiving the notice and supporting
7 documents from the former insurer.
8 C. The commissioner shall promulgate any rules and regulations, in
9 accordance with the Administrative Procedure Act, necessary to implement and
10 enforce this Section, including but not limited to rules regarding the procedures
11 for appeals and stays of the provisions of this Section.
12 D. As used in this Section, "former insurer" means an insurer with
13 whom the bail bond producer had a prior appointment and who is responsible
14 for any outstanding bonds written by the bail bond producer.
